HP Envy TouchSmart 15-J001TX Laptop (4th Gen Ci7x 8GBx 1TBx Win8x 2GB Graphx Touch)@@@I wanted a laptop which delivers high performance, had style, and was sufficiently heavy. This turned out to be the one for me. - It has a Great Touchpad, I would say almost as good as a Apple trackpad! I use all my fingers with the touchpad for great efficiency - Its extremely sleek design is pretty class. - The fingerprint scanner is pretty good, but unfortunately for me, my finger is unreadable. - Can open multiple applications without fear of crashing the system. - The touch screen is awesome, especially since I run a Windows 8 OS, and also android games can be played with the touchscreen. It is as though it is a huge Tab! - The battery stays for around 3 hours at high performance and around 4 hours at power saver mode, which is sufficient for me. - No CD Drive! I kept searching for a CD Drive for quite sometime before realising that there was'nt one. - Games like Splinter Cell, Tomb Raider 3 and PES run well, but the Nvidia GT graphic card does not perform as well as an Nvidia GTX. Cannot play games like NFS:Rivals and Assassins Creed IV, unless you want to play with extreme lag. - It heats up a bit when memory intensive applications such as games and video editors are running. - Data transfer with USBs are pretty fast, unless the USB is not good. - Does not make much noise, but as you keep using a definite hum is heard. - Price is a bit high, even though it is a great buy. This is a high performance laptop that can be used both for business and entertainment. I would recommend buying this product.
