Design: Brushed aluminium, does not retain fingerprints. sleek design. Indicators: Sleep, Low battery, Charging, Charged and HDD activity. All LED. Sound: Pretty loud, but don't expect woofer to give base even close to speakers. Display: 1080p, glossy. Touchscreen is very sensitive. People using Photoshop or Illustrator may have to reduce the resolution to be able to see properly. At 1080p icons for such software are too small. Also the viewing angle is a bit narrow for that perfect view. Performance: Not built for extreme gaming but can play Crisis 3 at mid settings. Mechanical hard rive so it takes time to book but most of the people will keep it on sleep most of the time and restart once a week so its not a deal breaker. You can upgrade to SSD but will have to do it on your own. Processor gives out decent performance. USB: 4 port all USB 3 capable. Gives 35 mbps for USB 2 devices (photos and videos). Touch screen and touch pad: Both are multi finger touch gesture, but many software will only detect pinch and rotate on touch pad. Touch screen does not support pinch and rotate function on most software (ex. adobe Photoshop and bridge). Flipkart: Quick delivery in good condition. All specs perfect. Only glitch is that there was an offer and they did not mention that it has a deadline. Also as the offer was from HP they did not take any care in informing how to avail it. Flipkart should improve in exchange of information regarding such schemes. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- After 2 months of use: Not Happy with the product. Updated to Windows 8.1 and it takes 2 mins to boot. I dont have any add ons at start up. its just basic booting time. Hangs at every update and the updates are also very frequent. You cannot directly download the latest driver from Nvidia, HP gives its modified driver to work with the system so its like having an android phone and waiter for the manufacturer to push the latest version. Does not support Wireless display as HP is giving it with Ralink adapter for wireless communication which is a bummer. My advice, throw in a bit more and get a mac which is much more stable and reliable. I don't recommend this product any more. ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- After 3 months: Please dont buy.
